[7] Greece, Athens suspected
Date: Sun 22 May 2022
Source: In-Cyprus [edited]
https://in-cyprus.philenews.com/a-suspected-case-of-monkeypox-examined-in-greece/


A suspected case of monkeypox infection is being examined, according to the Ministry of Health. It involves a British tourist who, together with his companion, asymptomatic, are transported to the 'Attikon' hospital in order to be treated in negative pressure rooms.

The National Public Health Organization (EODY) received samples for confirmatory examination which were sent to the reference laboratory, and the results will be available on Monday [23 May 2022].

--
