******
[8] USA, Florida
Date: Sun 22 May 2022
Source: Reuters [edited]
https://www.reuters.com/world/us/third-possible-case-monkeypox-found-us-2022-05-23/


Health authorities said they may have found a 3rd case of the monkeypox virus in the United States and are running tests on a patient in South Florida to confirm if the person has contracted the disease, which is staging a rare outbreak outside of Africa.

The case in Broward County, Florida, is "related to international travel," the US Centers for Disease Control and the Florida Department of Health said in a statement on Sunday [22 May 2022], "and the person remains isolated."

The results of tests conducted by the CDC are expected soon. No other cases have been identified in the state, the release said.

The 1st monkeypox case in the United States was reported in Massachusetts on Wednesday [18 May 2022]. The disease, which is similar to human smallpox but milder, was found in a man who had recently traveled to Canada. Health officials said the case posed no risk to the public.

[Byline: Rich Mckay]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED

[The report does not indicate where the international travel had occurred nor when the individual had arrived in Florida. Presumably, the monkeypox infection had not been acquired in Florida. - Mod.TY

